"The swings of the securities markets and investor behavior resemble the movement of a pendulum. And while we never know where we are going, we ought to know where we are."


- Howard Marks












David J. Hansen, J.D.

Principal, Portfolio Manager





Mr. Hansen is a Principal and Portfolio Manager, and he is responsible for overseeing D&G's Lexington office. Dave is a member of the firm's Asset Allocation Committee. Prior to joining D&G, Dave founded an investment partnership focusing on special situations and was a founder of CornerStone Bank, N.A., a community bank in Lexington, Virginia. Prior to moving to Lexington, he served as General Counsel of the publicly-traded Magellan Health Services in Atlanta, Georgia. Prior to working with Magellan, he was General Counsel of a start-up healthcare company. He began in the private practice of law with Alston & Bird and worked in Australia with King & Wood Mallesons.

Dave currently serves on the Board of Directors of CornerStone Bank, where he chairs the Nomination and Compensation Committee, and serves on the Audit and Asset and Liability Committees. Dave also serves on the Vestry at R.E. Lee Episcopal Church, and is a member of the Finance Committee. He is a past President of the Rockbridge Area Free Clinic. Dave has a B.A. in Economics and Philosophy from Vanderbilt University and a Juris Doctor from Washington and Lee University School of Law, where he was a Burks Scholar Teaching Fellow.









