"The essence of investment management is management of risks, not the management of returns. Well-managed portfolios start with this precept."


- Benjamin Graham












William W. Paxton, J.D., CFP®

Principal, Portfolio Manager





Mr. Paxton is a Principal and Portfolio Manager, and he serves on the firm's Investment and Asset Allocation Committees. Before joining D&G in 1996, Bill served as Associate Director of Development for Washington and Lee University. Prior to that, Bill was Southeast Region Director of Marketing and Leasing for a national real estate development firm. He began his professional career practicing general corporate law with the Richmond, Virginia-based firm of Williams Mullen.

Bill is an elder at First Presbyterian Church in Lynchburg and past Chairman of the church's Budget and Finance Committee. He has served as an officer or board member for a number of non-profit organizations in Central Virginia. Bill received his B.A. from Washington and Lee University and Juris Doctor from the University of Virginia School of Law. He holds the CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ certification.









