HP Inc. (NYSE:HPQ) Shares Bought by Oregon Public Employees Retirement Fund


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 19th, 2017 // No Comments




Oregon Public Employees Retirement Fund boosted its position in  HP Inc. (NYSE:HPQ) by 30.8% during the second quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 753,817 shares of the computer maker’s stock after buying an additional 177,700 shares during the period. Oregon Public Employees Retirement Fund’s holdings in HP were worth $13,177,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
A number of other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. First American Bank increased its position in  HP by 13.2% in the first quarter. First American Bank now owns 153,939 shares of the computer maker’s stock worth $2,752,000 after buying an additional 17,893 shares in the last quarter.  Quadrant Capital Group LLC increased its position in  HP by 0.4% in the first quarter. Quadrant Capital Group LLC now owns 29,540 shares of the computer maker’s stock worth $520,000 after buying an additional 116 shares in the last quarter.  Nexus Investment Management Inc. increased its position in  HP by 7.1% in the first quarter. Nexus Investment Management Inc. now owns 447,400 shares of the computer maker’s stock worth $8,000,000 after buying an additional 29,800 shares in the last quarter.  Burke & Herbert Bank & Trust Co. increased its position in  HP by 8.1% in the first quarter. Burke & Herbert Bank & Trust Co. now owns 27,573 shares of the computer maker’s stock worth $493,000 after buying an additional 2,060 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Creative Planning increased its position in  HP by 8.8% in the first quarter. Creative Planning now owns 93,512 shares of the computer maker’s stock worth $1,672,000 after buying an additional 7,585 shares in the last quarter. 79.49% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 


 Get HP Inc. alerts:



HP Inc. (HPQ) opened at 18.39 on Wednesday. The firm has a market capitalization of $30.96 billion, a PE ratio of 13.01 and a beta of 1.89. HP Inc. has a one year low of $13.55 and a one year high of $19.58. The company has a 50 day moving average price of $17.98 and a 200-day moving average price of $17.33. 





HP (NYSE:HPQ) last issued its earnings results on Wednesday, May 24th. The computer maker reported $0.40 EPS for the quarter, beating the consensus estimate of $0.39 by $0.01. The company had revenue of $12.40 billion during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $11.93 billion. HP had a net margin of 4.94% and a negative return on equity of 68.86%. The business’s revenue for the quarter was up 7.0% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter in the previous year, the company posted $0.41 EPS.  On average, equities analysts predict that  HP Inc. will post $1.64 EPS for the current year. 
The firm also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Wednesday, July 5th. Shareholders of record on Wednesday, June 14th were given a dividend of $0.1327 per share. This represents a $0.53 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 2.89%. The ex-dividend date  was Monday, June 12th. HP’s payout ratio is 37.32%. 
